.TH webp 1  "webp 0.1.0" 
.SH NAME
webp \- Command\-line tools for the webpkit WebP codec: libwebp\-style cwebp (lossy by default, \-lossless for VP8L) / dwebp and the webp brand tool.
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBwebp\fR [\fB\-v\fR|\fB\-\-verbose\fR]... [\fB\-q\fR|\fB\-\-quiet\fR] [\fB\-\-color\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fB\-V\fR|\fB\-\-version\fR] <\fIsubcommands\fR>
.SH DESCRIPTION
Command\-line tools for the webpkit WebP codec: libwebp\-style cwebp (lossy by default, \-lossless for VP8L) / dwebp and the webp brand tool.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
Print per\-stage detail on stderr
.TP
\fB\-q\fR, \fB\-\-quiet\fR
Suppress all non\-error output
.TP
\fB\-\-color\fR \fI<WHEN>\fR [default: auto]
auto, always, or never

`CLICOLOR_FORCE` and `NO_COLOR` are honored, and an explicit `\-\-color` outranks both. Left alone, messages are colored only when stderr is a terminal — so a pipe or a log file never receives escape codes.
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.TP
\fB\-V\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
Print version
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
webp\-decode(1)
Decode a WebP file to PNG (default), PPM/PAM, or raw pixels
.TP
webp\-encode(1)
Encode a PNG/PPM/PAM/raw image into a WebP file (lossless, or \-\-lossy)
.TP
webp\-convert(1)
Batch\-convert many images (or directories) to WebP, in parallel
.TP
webp\-info(1)
Print a summary of a WebP file (size, alpha, metadata, animation)
.TP
webp\-explain(1)
Explain an exit code: what a failing run\*(Aqs status number means
.TP
webp\-completions(1)
Print a shell completion script
.TP
webp\-man(1)
Print a man page in roff, for `man \-l \-` or a package\*(Aqs man directory
.TP
webp\-help(1)
Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)
.SH VERSION
v0.1.0
